ctRemNumConnections.name: ctRemNumConnections
ctRemNumConnections.description: This object describes the number of physical remote access connections on the platform.

ctRemPhysPortTable.name: ctRemPhysPortTable
ctRemPhysPortTable.description: A list of the descriptions of the physical remote access ports of this platform.

ctRemPhysPortEntry.name: ctRemPhysPortEntry
ctRemPhysPortEntry.description: A physical port entry. It contains objects relating to a given physical remote access port

ctRemConnectionIndex.name: ctRemConnectionIndex
ctRemConnectionIndex.description: A value indicating the remote connection this entry is located on.

ctRemPhysPortType.name: ctRemPhysPortType
ctRemPhysPortType.description: The type of physical port that this entry describes. None indicates that the physical port has no connector.

ctRemPhysPortSpecificMib.name: ctRemPhysPortSpecificMib
ctRemPhysPortSpecificMib.description: This object identifies an instance of the index object in the first group of objects in the MIB specific to the physical port.

ctRemPhysPortProtMgrType.name: ctRemPhysPortProtMgrType
ctRemPhysPortProtMgrType.description: This object identifies an instance of the type of Protocol Manager residing on this physical port. Before a physical port may be used, the type of manager must be designated. For example, if the physical port was going to be used as an ISDN PRI interface, with dial up PPP links, then the manager type would be set to (4), ISDN-PRI-PPP.

ctRemPhysPortProtMgrIfaceNum.name: ctRemPhysPortProtMgrIfaceNum
ctRemPhysPortProtMgrIfaceNum.description: This object identifies the interface number that will be assigned to the Protocol Managers IFO

ctRemPhysPortWanIfaceNum.name: ctRemPhysPortWanIfaceNum
ctRemPhysPortWanIfaceNum.description: This object identifies the interface number that will be assigned to the Wanio's IFO

ctRemPhysPortProtMgrMaxIfos.name: ctRemPhysPortProtMgrMaxIfos
ctRemPhysPortProtMgrMaxIfos.description: This object identifies the maximum number of IFO's that can be created on this physical interface.

ctRemPhysPortProtMgrIfaceList.name: ctRemPhysPortProtMgrIfaceList
ctRemPhysPortProtMgrIfaceList.description: This object identifies a list of interfaces that will be assigned to this Protocol Managers data IFO's

ctRemPhysAlarmTimeOut.name: ctRemPhysAlarmTimeOut
ctRemPhysAlarmTimeOut.description: Whenever the physical port is configured for nailed-up PPP this object specifies the time the physical port must remain in a failed state as a condition to begin the backup procedure. The backup procedure is begun for any active interface(s) that were connected over the failed physical port and which have been configured for backup.

ctRemPhysWpimType.name: ctRemPhysWpimType
ctRemPhysWpimType.description: This Mib object determines the Mode of operation that the T1/DDS Wpim module will function as. Setting a value of 1 will set the mode to DDS, setting a value of 2 will set the mode to T1.

ctRemInterfaceTable.name: ctRemInterfaceTable
ctRemInterfaceTable.description: The interface table for Cabletron remote interfaces. It is a list of items that are pertinant to the interfaces that are part of remote physical ports. The number of entries is dependent upon the total number of remote interfaces configured.

ctRemInterfaceEntry.name: ctRemInterfaceEntry
ctRemInterfaceEntry.description: A remote interface entry. It contains objects relating to an interface that is defined for remote Cabletron products.

ctRemIntEntIfIndex.name: ctRemIntEntIfIndex
ctRemIntEntIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface. This is the index of this entry in the ifTable.

ctRemIntEntCompression.name: ctRemIntEntCompression
ctRemIntEntCompression.description: This flag will indicate whether compression should take place on this interface.

ctRemIntEntCompRatio.name: ctRemIntEntCompRatio
ctRemIntEntCompRatio.description: This string indicates the current compression ratio on this interface.

ctRemIntEntCompStatus.name: ctRemIntEntCompStatus
ctRemIntEntCompStatus.description: This flag will indicate whether compression has been nogotiated on this interface.

ctRemIntEntMTU.name: ctRemIntEntMTU
ctRemIntEntMTU.description: The MTU to be negotiated for this interface. This will not be updated with the actual MTU, which can be found in the ifTable.

ctRemIntEntCongestion.name: ctRemIntEntCongestion
ctRemIntEntCongestion.description: This object identifies the Leaky Bucket algorithm flag for a Frame Relay circuit on this intertface. The option is supported when this flag is enabled, and not supported when this flag is disabled.

ctRemIntEntMaxProfiles.name: ctRemIntEntMaxProfiles
ctRemIntEntMaxProfiles.description: This object specifies the maximum number of neighbor profiles. A neighbor profile describes a possible connection. The maximum should be set to account for support of PPP multilink. That is to say, if PPP multilink is being used then the number of profiles must at least accomodate the maximum possible number of additional more BW connections. As such, each neighbor profile would then describe a possible connection to the same remote end point.

ctRemIntEntTxIdleTimeout.name: ctRemIntEntTxIdleTimeout
ctRemIntEntTxIdleTimeout.description: This object identifies the idle timeout value in which a packet needs to be transmitted before the interface is automatically disconnected. Allowed values are in increments of five seconds including zero.

ctRemIntEntRxIdleTimeout.name: ctRemIntEntRxIdleTimeout
ctRemIntEntRxIdleTimeout.description: This object identifies the idle timeout in which a packet needs to be received before the interface is automatically disconnected. Allowed values are in increments of five seconds including zero.

ctRemIntEntCircuitName.name: ctRemIntEntCircuitName
ctRemIntEntCircuitName.description: This object associates a circuit name with a specific interface.

ctRemIntEntEncryption.name: ctRemIntEntEncryption
ctRemIntEntEncryption.description: This flag will indicate whether encryption should take place on this interface.

ctRemIntEntEncryptStatus.name: ctRemIntEntEncryptStatus
ctRemIntEntEncryptStatus.description: This flag will indicate whether Encryption has been nogotiated on this interface.

ctRemPrimaryInterfaceTable.name: ctRemPrimaryInterfaceTable
ctRemPrimaryInterfaceTable.description: The interface table for Cabletron remote interfaces. It is a list of items that are pertinant to the interfaces that are part of remote physical ports. The number of entries is dependent upon the total number of remote interfaces configured.

ctRemPrimaryInterfaceEntry.name: ctRemPrimaryInterfaceEntry
ctRemPrimaryInterfaceEntry.description: A remote interface entry. It contains objects relating to an interface that is defined for remote Cabletron products.

ctRemPriIntEntIfIndex.name: ctRemPriIntEntIfIndex
ctRemPriIntEntIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface. This is the index of this entry in the ifTable.

ctRemPriIntEntConnectRetryInterval.name: ctRemPriIntEntConnectRetryInterval
ctRemPriIntEntConnectRetryInterval.description: This object specifies the interval in seconds between retries for restoring the primary interface.

ctRemBackupInterfaceTable.name: ctRemBackupInterfaceTable
ctRemBackupInterfaceTable.description: The interface table for Cabletron remote interfaces. It is a list of items that are pertinant to the interfaces that are part of remote physical ports. The number of entries is dependent upon the total number of remote interfaces configured.

ctRemBackupInterfaceEntry.name: ctRemBackupInterfaceEntry
ctRemBackupInterfaceEntry.description: A remote interface entry. It contains objects relating to an interface that is defined for remote Cabletron products.

ctRemIntEntBackupIfIndex.name: ctRemIntEntBackupIfIndex
ctRemIntEntBackupIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface. This is the index of this entry in the ifTable.

ctRemIntEntBackupIfNum.name: ctRemIntEntBackupIfNum
ctRemIntEntBackupIfNum.description: This object identifies which ifIndex will backup this interface in the event of a communications failure.

ctRemIntEntBackupIfInUseCnt.name: ctRemIntEntBackupIfInUseCnt
ctRemIntEntBackupIfInUseCnt.description: This object identifies how many other interfaces this interface will backup.

ctRemIntEntBackupIfTimeToConnect.name: ctRemIntEntBackupIfTimeToConnect
ctRemIntEntBackupIfTimeToConnect.description: This object identifies how long to wait in seconds before attempting to switchover to the backup interface. Allowed values are in increments of five seconds including zero.

ctRemIntEntBackupIfTimeToDisconnect.name: ctRemIntEntBackupIfTimeToDisconnect
ctRemIntEntBackupIfTimeToDisconnect.description: This object identifies how long to wait in seconds before attempting to switchover to the primary interface. Allowed values are in increments of five seconds including zero.

ctRemIntEntBackupIfOverride.name: ctRemIntEntBackupIfOverride
ctRemIntEntBackupIfOverride.description: This object identifies if the interface will switch back to the primary link after it has become active again. A force condition will not allow the interface to switch back.

ctRemIntEntBackupConnectRetries.name: ctRemIntEntBackupConnectRetries
ctRemIntEntBackupConnectRetries.description: This object specifies the number of tries to bring-up the backup interface before giving up.

ctRemIntEntBackupConnectRetryInterval.name: ctRemIntEntBackupConnectRetryInterval
ctRemIntEntBackupConnectRetryInterval.description: This object specifies the interval in seconds between retries for bringing up backup interface before giving up.

ctRemExtPhysPortTable.name: ctRemExtPhysPortTable
ctRemExtPhysPortTable.description: A list of the descriptions of the physical remote access ports of this platform.

ctRemExtPhysPortEntry.name: ctRemExtPhysPortEntry
ctRemExtPhysPortEntry.description: A physical port entry. It contains objects relating to a given physical remote access port

ctRemExtConnectionIndex.name: ctRemExtConnectionIndex
ctRemExtConnectionIndex.description: A value indicating the remote connection this entry is located on.

ctRemExtProtMgrIndex.name: ctRemExtProtMgrIndex
ctRemExtProtMgrIndex.description: A value indicating the protMgr number for this entry.

ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrType.name: ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrType
ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrType.description: This object identifies an instance of the type of Protocol Manager residing on this physical port. Before a physical port may be used, the type of manager must be designated. For example, if the physical port was going to be used as an ISDN PRI interface, with dial up PPP links, then the manager type would be set to (4), ISDN-PRI-PPP.

ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrEnable.name: ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrEnable
ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrEnable.description: This object identifies an instance of the the enable flag of Protocol Manager residing on this physical port.

ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrIfaceNum.name: ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrIfaceNum
ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrIfaceNum.description: This object identifies the interface number that will be assigned to the Protocol Managers IFO

ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrMaxIfos.name: ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrMaxIfos
ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrMaxIfos.description: This object identifies the maximum number of IFO's that can be created on this physical interface.

ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrIfaceList.name: ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrIfaceList
ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrIfaceList.description: This object identifies a list of interfaces that will be assigned to this Protocol Managers data IFO's

ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrChannelList.name: ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrChannelList
ctRemExtPhysPortProtMgrChannelList.description: This object identifies a list of channles/timeslots that will be assigned to this Protocol Managers data IFO's

ctDs1ExtensionsTable.name: ctDs1ExtensionsTable
ctDs1ExtensionsTable.description: This table is an extension to the standard ds1 configuration table. It is a list of items that are pertinant to ds1 ports on a platform. There is one entry per ds1 physical port on the platform.

ctDs1ExtensionsEntry.name: ctDs1ExtensionsEntry
ctDs1ExtensionsEntry.description: A ds1 extensions entry containing objects relating to the particular ds1 physical port.

ctDs1ExtensionsEntryIndex.name: ctDs1ExtensionsEntryIndex
ctDs1ExtensionsEntryIndex.description: A unique value for each ds1 physical port on the platform.

ctDs1ExtensionsNumInterfaces.name: ctDs1ExtensionsNumInterfaces
ctDs1ExtensionsNumInterfaces.description: The number of interfaces on this physical port. This number inidicates the number of entries this physical port uses in the ifTable.

ctDs1ExtensionsToggleFracTable.name: ctDs1ExtensionsToggleFracTable
ctDs1ExtensionsToggleFracTable.description: Setting this object to 1 will cause the Ds1 Fractional Table to be updated with the new values, as entered. Setting this object to 2, will cause the Ds1 Fractional Table to view as the table being entered. Setting this object to 3, will cause the Ds1 Fractional Table to be the table that is currently in use, regardless of any changes being entered. Setting this object to 4, will cause any changes that have been made to the Ds1 Fractional Table since the last update-table to be deleted. For physical ports that are of type synch, or for Ds1 ports that do not support the Ds1 Fractional Table, this object will have no affect, and will always return a 1.

ctDs1ExtensionsLineBuildOut.name: ctDs1ExtensionsLineBuildOut
ctDs1ExtensionsLineBuildOut.description: The line build out setting for this ds1 physical port. Unknown indicates that the setting is neither readable or writable.

ctDs1ExtensionsCFADuration.name: ctDs1ExtensionsCFADuration
ctDs1ExtensionsCFADuration.description: The length of time (in seconds), that the ds1 port will remain in the Carrier Failure Alarm state after the alarm condition has cleared. For those Ds1 ports not supporting Carrier Failure Alarm duration, this object always returns 1, and setting the object has no effect.

ctDs1ExtensionsDIEnable.name: ctDs1ExtensionsDIEnable
ctDs1ExtensionsDIEnable.description: Enables or disables Drop and Insert functionality on a D/I WPIM. If enabled, all zero assigned timeslots will designate D/I interface channels, if disabled all zero channels will designate dummy channels as on a T1 or E1.

ctDs1ExtensionsTotalValidIntervals.name: ctDs1ExtensionsTotalValidIntervals
ctDs1ExtensionsTotalValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which valid data was collected for the DS1 mib, which is currently RFC1406. This counter is similar to RFC1406 dsx1ValidIntervals except that the count represents the total number of complete 15 minute intervals since the ds1 interface has been online, and does not stop at the 24 hour period.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestMode.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestMode
wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestMode.description: This object is used to request that a type of process be in control of the testing function. This is used to differentiate between automated test procedures and those manually controlled by a user. When read, this object reflects which type of process is actually in control of the testing function. The implementation is free to prioritize or deny requests in a proprietary manner.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertRun.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertRun
wanDs1ExtensionsBertRun.description: Controls the sending of test data over this physical port. The data is a pattern described by wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestPattern.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertCurrentResults.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertCurrentResults
wanDs1ExtensionsBertCurrentResults.description: Indicates the results of the testing for the last completed sampling period. A non-negative number is the error rate in bits per million bits.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertCumulativeResults.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertCumulativeResults
wanDs1ExtensionsBertCumulativeResults.description: Indicates the total number of errors since the testing was enabled. It is not a rate.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertPeakResults.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertPeakResults
wanDs1ExtensionsBertPeakResults.description: Indicates the highest value of wanDs1ExtensionsBertCurrentResults since the testing was enabled. A non-negative number is the error rate in bits per million bits.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertAverageResult.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertAverageResult
wanDs1ExtensionsBertAverageResult.description: Indicates the average value of wanDs1ExtensionsBertCurrentResults since the testing was enabled. A non-negative number is the error rate in bits per million bits.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestPattern.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestPattern
wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestPattern.description: This object is used to specify the pattern of the test data.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertSamplePeriod.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertSamplePeriod
wanDs1ExtensionsBertSamplePeriod.description: This object is the duration of time in seconds at which the current test results will be periodically written to wanDs1ExtensionsBertCurrentResults. The range is 1 to 3600, with a default value of 10.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertNumPeriods.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertNumPeriods
wanDs1ExtensionsBertNumPeriods.description: The number of sampling periods that have elapsed during the current test run.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestTraps.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestTraps
wanDs1ExtensionsBertTestTraps.description: This object is used to enable or disable the sending of a trap at the conclusion of the measurement period. The trap will contain the information described by ctDs1BertCurrentResults. The default value is disabled.

wanDs1ExtensionsBertDataStatus.name: wanDs1ExtensionsBertDataStatus
wanDs1ExtensionsBertDataStatus.description: This object provides the operating status of the transmission of test data packets.

ctDs1WanDriverTable.name: ctDs1WanDriverTable
ctDs1WanDriverTable.description: This table is an extension to the standard ds1 configuration table. It is a list of items that are pertinant to the hdlc driver on a platform. There is one entry per ds1 physical port on the platform.

ctDs1WanDriverEntry.name: ctDs1WanDriverEntry
ctDs1WanDriverEntry.description: A ds1 wan driver entry containing objects relating to the particular ds1 physical port pertaining to a specific channel on the wan driver chip.

ctDs1WanDriverEntryIndex.name: ctDs1WanDriverEntryIndex
ctDs1WanDriverEntryIndex.description: A unique value for each ds1 physical port on the platform.

ctDs1WanDriverChannelIndex.name: ctDs1WanDriverChannelIndex
ctDs1WanDriverChannelIndex.description: A unique value for each channel on a wan driver on the platform.

ctDs1WanDriverLineCode.name: ctDs1WanDriverLineCode
ctDs1WanDriverLineCode.description: This object controls the individual channels line coding on a wan driver device on the platform.

ctDs1WanDriverCRCBits.name: ctDs1WanDriverCRCBits
ctDs1WanDriverCRCBits.description: This object controls the individual channels CRC bits generation on a wan driver device on the platform.

ctRs232ExtensionsTable.name: ctRs232ExtensionsTable
ctRs232ExtensionsTable.description: This table is an extension to the standard rs232-like mib. It is a list of items that are pertinant to rs232-like ports on a platform. There is one entry per synchronous physical port on the platform.

ctRs232ExtensionsEntry.name: ctRs232ExtensionsEntry
ctRs232ExtensionsEntry.description: A rs232-like extensions entry containing objects relating to the particular rs232-like physical port.

ctRs232ExtensionsEntryIndex.name: ctRs232ExtensionsEntryIndex
ctRs232ExtensionsEntryIndex.description: A unique value for each rs232-like physical port on the platform.

ctRs232ExtensionsCTSEnable.name: ctRs232ExtensionsCTSEnable
ctRs232ExtensionsCTSEnable.description: This object indicates whether the platform should generate CTS. When disabled the platform will not generate CTS, when enabled, the platform will generate CTS. The actual state of the CTS line is available in the rs-232 like mib.

ctRs232ExtensionsDSREnable.name: ctRs232ExtensionsDSREnable
ctRs232ExtensionsDSREnable.description: This object indicates whether the platform should generate DSR. When disabled the platform will not generate DSR, when enabled, the platform will generate DSR. The actual state of the DSR line is available in the rs-232 like mib.

ctRs232ExtensionsRTSEnable.name: ctRs232ExtensionsRTSEnable
ctRs232ExtensionsRTSEnable.description: This object indicates whether the platform should generate RTS. When disabled the platform will not generate RTS, when enabled, the platform will generate RTS. The actual state of the RTS line is available in the rs-232 like mib.

ctRs232ExtensionsDTREnable.name: ctRs232ExtensionsDTREnable
ctRs232ExtensionsDTREnable.description: This object indicates whether the platform should generate DTR. When disabled the platform will not generate DSR, when enabled, the platform will generate DTR. The actual state of the DTR line is available in the rs-232 like mib.

frDcpCircuitTable.name: frDcpCircuitTable
frDcpCircuitTable.description: A table containing data compression information about specific Data Link Connection Identifiers and corresponding virtual circuit. This information is used to support the frCircuitTable following RFC-1315.

frDcpCircuitEntry.name: frDcpCircuitEntry
frDcpCircuitEntry.description: The data compression information regarding a single Data Link Connection Identifier.

frDcpCircuitIfIndex.name: frDcpCircuitIfIndex
frDcpCircuitIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of ifEntry that this DCP virtual circuit object is layered onto.

frDcpCircuitDlci.name: frDcpCircuitDlci
frDcpCircuitDlci.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.6
frDcpCircuitDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier for this DCP virtual circuit object.

frDcpCircuitEnable.name: frDcpCircuitEnable
frDcpCircuitEnable.description: Indicates whether data compression should take place on this particular end side virtual circuit.

frDcpCircuitStatus.name: frDcpCircuitStatus
frDcpCircuitStatus.description: On indicates that the compression has been successfully negotiated and is operating. Off indicates that the compression negotiation has failed and compression is not operating at this time, or compression has been terminated by either peer.

frDcpCircuitRatio.name: frDcpCircuitRatio
frDcpCircuitRatio.description: The ratio of uncompressed to compressed transmitted data. If the data compression status is off, 1:1 will be displayed.

ctDDSConfigEntry.name: ctDDSConfigEntry
ctDDSConfigEntry.description: An Entry in the DDS Configuration Table

ctDDSLineIndex.name: ctDDSLineIndex
ctDDSLineIndex.description: A unique value for each ds1 physical port on the platform.

ctDDSIfIndex.name: ctDDSIfIndex
ctDDSIfIndex.description: Index associated with this dds physical port

ctDDSLineMode.name: ctDDSLineMode
ctDDSLineMode.description: DDS-PRI is full duplex 56k link, No framing in loop data so loop speed is also 56k. Data stream: --d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7-- DDS-SC is also full duplex 56k link, requires framing bits to distinguish between primary and secondary channels. --d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7 F C/S-- where F is framing bit and C/S for secondary channel as well as used for control bit. With these two extra bits the loop speed is increased to 72k. primary channel rate is 56k. DDS-CC is full duplex 64k link. Does not require framing bit but uses a same format as SC, nineth bit position is lumped with primary channel and not used for control. Loop speed is 72k, Primary channel rate is 64k. --d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7 F d8--

ctDDSLineCoding.name: ctDDSLineCoding
ctDDSLineCoding.description: This object describes the variety of Zero Code suppression on this interface. JBZS refers to Jammed Bit Zero suppresion, which forces a 1 bit every 8 bit periods. None refers to a mode in which some other means is used to insure pulse density requirements.

ctDDSLoopbackConfig.name: ctDDSLoopbackConfig
ctDDSLoopbackConfig.description: This variable represents the loopback configuration of the DDS interface. ddsNoLoop means the interface is not in loopback state, ddsLocalLoop means the signal is transmitted and looped back to the same interface, ddsLineLoop means the received signal at this interface does not go through the device but is looped back out, and ddsOtherLoop represents a loop not defined here.

ctDDSLineStatus.name: ctDDSLineStatus
ctDDSLineStatus.description: This variable describes the current operational status of DDS line.

ctDDSTxClockSource.name: ctDDSTxClockSource
ctDDSTxClockSource.description: The source of Transmit clock. 'ddsLoopTiming' indicates that the recovered receive clock is used as transmit clock. 'ddsLocalTiming' indicates that a local clock source is used. 'ddsThroughTiming' indicates that recovered receive clock from another interface is used as transmit clock.

ctDDSPortInSpeed.name: ctDDSPortInSpeed
ctDDSPortInSpeed.description: This variable describes the current operational receive speed of DDS line. It is a read only value based entirely on DDS type (CC or PRI).

ctDDSPortOutSpeed.name: ctDDSPortOutSpeed
ctDDSPortOutSpeed.description: This variable describes the current operational transmit speed of DDS line. It is a read only value based entirely on DDS type CC or PRI

ctPppCountersTable.name: ctPppCountersTable
ctPppCountersTable.description: Table containing the parameters for the local PPP entity related to the counters and timers.

ctPppCountersEntry.name: ctPppCountersEntry
ctPppCountersEntry.description: PPP counter/timer information for a particular PPP link.

ctPppCountersIfIndex.name: ctPppCountersIfIndex
ctPppCountersIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface. This is the index of this entry in the ifTable.

ctPppCountersMaxTerminate.name: ctPppCountersMaxTerminate
ctPppCountersMaxTerminate.description: MaxTerminate indicates the number of Terminate- Request packets sent without receiving a Terminate-Ack before assuming that the peer in unable to respond.

ctPppCountersMaxConfigure.name: ctPppCountersMaxConfigure
ctPppCountersMaxConfigure.description: MaxConfigure indicates the number of Configure- Request packets sent without receiving a Configure-Ack, Configre-Nak or Configure-Reject before assuming that the peer in unable to respond.

ctPppCountersMaxFailure.name: ctPppCountersMaxFailure
ctPppCountersMaxFailure.description: MaxFailure indicates the number of Configure-Nak packets sent without sending a Configure-Ack before assuming that the configuration is not converging. Any further Configure-Reject packets for peer requested options are converted to Configure-Reject packets, and locally desires options are no longer appended.

ctPppCountersRestartTimer.name: ctPppCountersRestartTimer
ctPppCountersRestartTimer.description: The Restart timer is used to time transmissions of Configure-Request and Terminate-Request packets. Expiration of the Restart-Timer causes a Timeout event, and retransmission of the corresponding Configure-Request or Terminate-Request packet.

ctPppLcpExtTable.name: ctPppLcpExtTable
ctPppLcpExtTable.description: Table containing the parameters for the local PPP entity related to the counters and timers.

ctPppLcpExtEntry.name: ctPppLcpExtEntry
ctPppLcpExtEntry.description: PPP LCP configurationinformation for a particular PPP link.

ctPppLcpExtIfIndex.name: ctPppLcpExtIfIndex
ctPppLcpExtIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface. This is the index of this entry in the ifTable.

ctPppLcpExtAuthenticationProt.name: ctPppLcpExtAuthenticationProt
ctPppLcpExtAuthenticationProt.description: Enables a particular authentication protocol on this PPP link(now modified for read-only.

ctPppLcpExtQualityProt.name: ctPppLcpExtQualityProt
ctPppLcpExtQualityProt.description: Enables a particular link-quality protocol on this PPP link.

ctPppLcpExtPFC.name: ctPppLcpExtPFC
ctPppLcpExtPFC.description: Enables protocol field compression on this PPP link.

ctPppLcpExtACFC.name: ctPppLcpExtACFC
ctPppLcpExtACFC.description: Enables address and control field compression on this PPP link.

ctPppLcpExtSelfDescribePadding.name: ctPppLcpExtSelfDescribePadding
ctPppLcpExtSelfDescribePadding.description: This Configuration Option provides a method for an implementation to indicate to the peer that it understands self-describing pads when padding is added at the end of the PPP Information field.

ctPppLcpExtCallback.name: ctPppLcpExtCallback
ctPppLcpExtCallback.description: This Configuration Option provides a method for an implementation to request a dial-up peer to call back.

ctPppLcpExtCompoundFrames.name: ctPppLcpExtCompoundFrames
ctPppLcpExtCompoundFrames.description: This Configuration Option provides a method for an implementation to send multiple PPP encapsulated packets within the same frame.

ctPppLcpExtEchoRequest.name: ctPppLcpExtEchoRequest
ctPppLcpExtEchoRequest.description: A zero indicated no Echo Request and any other value provides an interval to send Echo-Requests to the Peer. The Echo-Request provides a Data Link Layer loopback mechanism for use in exercising both directions of the link. This is useful in debugging, link quality determination. LCP MUST be in the OPENED state for an Echo-Request to occur.

ctPppLcpExtReplyCounter.name: ctPppLcpExtReplyCounter
ctPppLcpExtReplyCounter.description: Increments a counter if the Local Device correctly received an Echo-Reply from the Peer. LCP MUST be in the OPENED state for an Echo-Reply to occur.

ctPppLcpExtMpCapable.name: ctPppLcpExtMpCapable
ctPppLcpExtMpCapable.description: Multilink Protocol (MP) option selector. Set to a value of one when MP support is desired otherwise set to a value of two. The default value is two. When set to two the attempt is made to negotiate MP support. MP support is symmetrical.

ctPppBncpExtTable.name: ctPppBncpExtTable
ctPppBncpExtTable.description: Table containing the parameters for the local PPP entity related to the counters and timers.

ctPppBncpExtEntry.name: ctPppBncpExtEntry
ctPppBncpExtEntry.description: PPP LCP configuration information for a particular PPP link.

ctPppBncpExtIfIndex.name: ctPppBncpExtIfIndex
ctPppBncpExtIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface. This is the index of this entry in the ifTable.

ctPppBncpExtCrcStatus.name: ctPppBncpExtCrcStatus
ctPppBncpExtCrcStatus.description: Enables and disables CRC status. First our platform must support CRC. If the platform does, then setting to disabled will not send CRC. The default is enabled, which sends CRC.

ctPppMpExtTable.name: ctPppMpExtTable
ctPppMpExtTable.description: Table containing the parameters for the local PPP entity related to the counters and timers.

ctPppMpExtEntry.name: ctPppMpExtEntry
ctPppMpExtEntry.description: PPP LCP configurationinformation for a particular PPP link.

ctPppMpExtIfIndex.name: ctPppMpExtIfIndex
ctPppMpExtIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface. This is the index of this entry in the ifTable.

ctPppLcpExtMpLUT.name: ctPppLcpExtMpLUT
ctPppLcpExtMpLUT.description: Used to set the Line Utilization Threshold (LUT) % value to compare against the linear weighted percentage by which to determine when more/less bandwidth is to be added/removed. Linear weighting is averaged over the period of time specified by ctPppLcpExtMpHistoryTime.

ctPppLcpExtMpHistoryTime.name: ctPppLcpExtMpHistoryTime
ctPppLcpExtMpHistoryTime.description: Used to set the history time value in seconds for the number of line utilization reading(s) desired to compute the average line utilization. That is to say, it specifies the window size over which to compute the average line utilization.

ctPppLcpExtMpMoreBW.name: ctPppLcpExtMpMoreBW
ctPppLcpExtMpMoreBW.description: Used to set the number of consecutive line utilization average readings that must exceed ctPppLcpExtMpLUT as a condition of when to increase the bandwidth if more BW is permitted.

ctPppLcpExtMpLessBW.name: ctPppLcpExtMpLessBW
ctPppLcpExtMpLessBW.description: Used to set the number of consecutive line utilization average readings that must fall below ctPppLcpExtMpLUT as a condition of when to remove possible previously added bandwidth.

ctPppLcpExtMpMaxChannels.name: ctPppLcpExtMpMaxChannels
ctPppLcpExtMpMaxChannels.description: Used to set the maxium number of channels an MP capable connection is allowed.

ctPppLcpExtMpChannelsToAdd.name: ctPppLcpExtMpChannelsToAdd
ctPppLcpExtMpChannelsToAdd.description: Used to set the number of additional channel(s) to increment by whenever the need for more bandwidth is determined.

ctPppLcpExtMpChannelsToRemove.name: ctPppLcpExtMpChannelsToRemove
ctPppLcpExtMpChannelsToRemove.description: Used to set the number of channel(s) to decrement by whenever the need for possible previously added bandwidth is determined to no longer be needed.

ctPppEcpExtTable.name: ctPppEcpExtTable
ctPppEcpExtTable.description: Table containing the parameters for the local PPP entity related to the encrpytion control protocol.

ctPppEcpExtEntry.name: ctPppEcpExtEntry
ctPppEcpExtEntry.description: PPP ECP configuration information for a particular PPP link.

ctPppEcpExtIfIndex.name: ctPppEcpExtIfIndex
ctPppEcpExtIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface. This is the index of this entry in the ifTable.

ctPppEcpKey.name: ctPppEcpKey
ctPppEcpKey.description: A 56-bit key (14 hex characters) used for the DES encryption.

ctPppEcpIV.name: ctPppEcpIV
ctPppEcpIV.description: A 64-bit initialization vector (16 hex characters) used for the DES encryption in CBC mode.

ctWanalyzerTable.name: ctWanalyzerTable
ctWanalyzerTable.description: Table containing the parameters for the local Wanalyzer entity related to the configured Protocol.

ctWanalyzerIfIndex.name: ctWanalyzerIfIndex
ctWanalyzerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface. This is the index of this entry in the ifTable.

ctWanalyzerEnabled.name: ctWanalyzerEnabled
ctWanalyzerEnabled.description: This Persistent Object is a flag which indicates whether or not the WANalyzer is enabled or disabled. Upon system initialization this flag defaults to disabled unless a value for this object is found in NVRAM.

ctWanalyzerMaxEntries.name: ctWanalyzerMaxEntries
ctWanalyzerMaxEntries.description: This Persistent Object is an integer greater than 1 which specifies the maximum total number of entries which the table will handle. When the WANalyzer is enabled this value defaults to a value dependent on the implementation unless a value is found in NVRAM.

ctWanalyzerClearAll.name: ctWanalyzerClearAll
ctWanalyzerClearAll.description: When set to 2, the entire table of entries is cleared. Upon clearing of the table, this value is reset to 1. This object is not present if the WANalyzer is disabled.

ctWanalyzerClearInterface.name: ctWanalyzerClearInterface
ctWanalyzerClearInterface.description: When set to 2, all entries for this MIB-II interface index will be removed from the table. Upon complete removal of those entries, this value is reset to 1. This object is not present if the WANalyzer is disabled.

ctWanalyzerDisplayInterface.name: ctWanalyzerDisplayInterface
ctWanalyzerDisplayInterface.description: When set to a valid MIB-II interface number, the table displays only those entries in the table which were received from that MIB-II interface. This value is set to -1 upon initialization and indicates that entries from all interfaces will be displayed. This object is not present if the WANalyzer is disabled.

ctWanalyzerCurrEntries.name: ctWanalyzerCurrEntries
ctWanalyzerCurrEntries.description: A non-negative integer indicating the current number of entries in the table. This object is not present if the WANalyzer is disabled.

wanalyzerMessageTable.name: wanalyzerMessageTable
wanalyzerMessageTable.description: A table containing all of the message entries for this device. If the WANalyzer is disabled, this table will not be present.

wanalyzerEntry.name: wanalyzerEntry
wanalyzerEntry.description: A message entry in the WANalyzer table corresponding to a particular interface in a particular instance.

wanMessageIndex.name: wanMessageIndex
wanMessageIndex.description: An integer between 1 and wanalyzerMaxEntries which indicates the overall position this entry has in the WANalyzer table.

wanMessageInterfaceIndex.name: wanMessageInterfaceIndex
wanMessageInterfaceIndex.description: The MIB-II interface index representing the interface which sent this message.

wanMessageDate.name: wanMessageDate
wanMessageDate.description: The date when this message was received by the WANalyzer in the standard MMDDYY format.

wanMessageTime.name: wanMessageTime
wanMessageTime.description: The time of day when this message was received by the WANalyzer in the standard HHMMSS format.

wanMessageCode.name: wanMessageCode
wanMessageCode.description: An enumerated value representing the nature of the debug message sent by the interface.

ds1AlarmGlobalAdmin.name: ds1AlarmGlobalAdmin
ds1AlarmGlobalAdmin.description: Used to enable and disable the DS1 Alarm Monitoring Application for all DS1 circuits on the device.

ds1AlarmGlobalAutoRecovery.name: ds1AlarmGlobalAutoRecovery
ds1AlarmGlobalAutoRecovery.description: Used to enable and disable the DS1 Alarm Automatic Recovery feature for all DS1 circuits on the device. For those devices that support ds1 alarm monitoring, but do not support the automatic recovery feature, this object always returns disabled, and performs no action when written.

ds1AlarmGlobalTrapEnable.name: ds1AlarmGlobalTrapEnable
ds1AlarmGlobalTrapEnable.description: Used to enable and disable the DS1 Alarm SNMP Trap generation feature for all DS1 circuits on the device. This object operates in conjunction with configuration of objects in the ctron-trap-mib.txt

ds1AlarmGlobalESCount.name: ds1AlarmGlobalESCount
ds1AlarmGlobalESCount.description: Used in conjuction with ctDs1AlarmESInterval to set the threshold for alarm generation when the number of Errored Seconds for a specified time interval, measured in minutes, is exceeded. The default Errored Seconds alarm condition is 100 errored seconds over a 6 minute time interval.

ds1AlarmGlobalESInterval.name: ds1AlarmGlobalESInterval
ds1AlarmGlobalESInterval.description: Used in conjuction with ds1AlarmGlobalESCount to set the threshold for alarm generation when the number of Errored Seconds for a specified time interval, measured in minutes, is exceeded. The default Errored Seconds alarm condition is 100 errored seconds over a 6 minute time interval.

ds1AlarmGlobalBPVErrorRate.name: ds1AlarmGlobalBPVErrorRate
ds1AlarmGlobalBPVErrorRate.description: Used to specify the negative exponent of 10, used in monitoring Bipolar Violations (Code Violations for E1) over intervals defined by ds1AlarmGlobalBPVInterval. For example, for a ds1AlarmGlobalBPVErrorRate value of 6 used with a ds1AlarmGlobalBPVInterval of 15, an alarm is generated when a 15 minute period has an average error rate which exceeds 1 Bipolar Violation (Code Violation for E1) per million bits. For those devices that support ds1 alarm monitoring but who's hardware does not support detect bipolar violations, this object always returns the default, and performs no action when written.

ds1AlarmGlobalBPVInterval.name: ds1AlarmGlobalBPVInterval
ds1AlarmGlobalBPVInterval.description: Used to specify the interval, used in monitoring Bipolar Violations (Code Violations for E1) with thresholds defined by ds1AlarmGlobalBPVErrorRate. For example, for a ds1AlarmGlobalBPVErrorRate value of 6 used with a ds1AlarmGlobalBPVInterval of 15, an alarm is generated when a 15 minute period has an average error rate which exceeds 1 Bipolar Violation (Code Violation for E1) per million bits. For those devices that support ds1 alarm monitoring but who's hardware does not detect bipolar violations, this object always returns the default, and performs no action when written.

ds1AlarmGlobalManualRecovery.name: ds1AlarmGlobalManualRecovery
ds1AlarmGlobalManualRecovery.description: To cause a manual recovery to occur on all Ds1 circuits, this object is set to a 1. It is always read as a 1. The recovery will occur only when automatic recovery is disabled.

ds1AlarmConfigTable.name: ds1AlarmConfigTable
ds1AlarmConfigTable.description: Table containing objects used to configure DS1 alarm functionality on a per DS1 basis.

ds1AlarmConfigEntry.name: ds1AlarmConfigEntry
ds1AlarmConfigEntry.description: A description of a single entry.

ds1PhysNum.name: ds1PhysNum
ds1PhysNum.description: The value for this object is equal to the value of a unique physical connection identifier associated with this DS1 which is clearly labeled on the device. For those products that do not have a DS1 identifier labeled on the device, the value for this object is the same as rfc1406 dsx1LineIndex.

ds1AlarmAdmin.name: ds1AlarmAdmin
ds1AlarmAdmin.description: Used to enable and disable the DS1 Alarm Monitoring Application for this DS1 circuit.

ds1AlarmAutoRecovery.name: ds1AlarmAutoRecovery
ds1AlarmAutoRecovery.description: Used to enable and disable the DS1 Alarm Automatic Recovery feature for this DS1 circuit. For those devices that support ds1 alarm monitoring, but do not support the automatic recovery feature, this object always returns disabled, and performs no action when written.

ds1AlarmTrapEnable.name: ds1AlarmTrapEnable
ds1AlarmTrapEnable.description: Used to enable and disable the DS1 Alarm SNMP Trap generation feature for this DS1 circuit. This object operates in conjunction with configuration of objects in the ctron-trap-mib.txt

ds1AlarmESCount.name: ds1AlarmESCount
ds1AlarmESCount.description: Used in conjuction with ctDs1AlarmESInterval to set the threshold for alarm generation when the number of Errored Seconds for a specified time interval, measured in minutes, is exceeded. The default Errored Seconds alarm condition is 100 errored seconds over a 6 minute time interval.

ds1AlarmESInterval.name: ds1AlarmESInterval
ds1AlarmESInterval.description: Used in conjuction with ctDs1AlarmESCount to set the threshold for alarm generation when the number of Errored Seconds for a specified time interval, measured in minutes, is exceeded. The default Errored Seconds alarm condition is 100 errored seconds over a 6 minute time interval.

ds1AlarmBPVErrorRate.name: ds1AlarmBPVErrorRate
ds1AlarmBPVErrorRate.description: Used to specify the negative exponent of 10, used in monitoring Bipolar Violations (Code Violations for E1) over intervals defined by ds1AlarmBPVInterval. For example, for a ds1AlarmBPVErrorRate value of 6 used with a ds1AlarmBPVInterval of 15, an alarm is generated when a 15 minute period has an average error rate which exceeds 1 Bipolar Violation (Code Violation for E1) per million bits. For those devices that support ds1 alarm monitoring but who's hardware does not support detect bipolar violations, this object always returns the default, and performs no action when written.

ds1AlarmBPVInterval.name: ds1AlarmBPVInterval
ds1AlarmBPVInterval.description: Used to specify the interval, used in monitoring Bipolar Violations (Code Violations for E1) with thresholds defined by ds1AlarmBPVErrorRate. For example, for a ds1AlarmBPVErrorRate value of 6 used with a ds1AlarmBPVInterval of 15, an alarm is generated when a 15 minute period has an average error rate which exceeds 1 Bipolar Violation (Code Violation for E1) per million bits. For those devices that support ds1 alarm monitoring but who's hardware does not support detect bipolar violations, this object always returns the default, and performs no action when written.

ds1AlarmManualRecovery.name: ds1AlarmManualRecovery
ds1AlarmManualRecovery.description: To cause a manual recovery to occur, this object is set to a 1. It is always read as a 1. The recovery will occur only when automatic recovery is disabled.

ipPQAdmin.name: ipPQAdmin
ipPQAdmin.description: Used to enable and disable the IP Priority Queue Forwarding Application.

iPPQMaxEntries.name: iPPQMaxEntries
iPPQMaxEntries.description: Returns the maximum number of IP address entries supported by the IP Priority Queue application on this device.

iPPQNumEntries.name: iPPQNumEntries
iPPQNumEntries.description: Get the number of IP address entries currently programmed in the ipPQAddressTable.

iPPQAddAddress.name: iPPQAddAddress
iPPQAddAddress.description: Add an IP address to the ipPQAddressTable. Always read as a 0.0.0.0.

iPPQDelAddress.name: iPPQDelAddress
iPPQDelAddress.description: Delete an IP address from the ipPQAddressTable. Always read as a 0.0.0.0.

ipPQAddressTable.name: ipPQAddressTable
ipPQAddressTable.description: Table containing IP addresses, used in an IP Priority Queue Forwarding function.

ipPQAddressEntry.name: ipPQAddressEntry
ipPQAddressEntry.description: A description of a single entry.

ipPQAddressId.name: ipPQAddressId
ipPQAddressId.description: A unique value identifying an element in a sequence of IP PQ address entries.

ipPQIPAddress.name: ipPQIPAddress
ipPQIPAddress.description: Returns an IP address associated with a specific entry in this table.

ctDs3ExtensionsTable.name: ctDs3ExtensionsTable
ctDs3ExtensionsTable.description: This table is an extension to the standard ds3 configuration table. It is a list of items that are pertinant to ds3 ports on a platform. There is one entry per ds3 physical port on the platform.

ctDs3ExtensionsEntry.name: ctDs3ExtensionsEntry
ctDs3ExtensionsEntry.description: A ds3 extensions entry containing objects relating to the particular ds3 physical port.

ctDs3ExtensionsEntryIndex.name: ctDs3ExtensionsEntryIndex
ctDs3ExtensionsEntryIndex.description: A unique value for each ds3 physical port on the platform.

ctDs3ExtensionsNumInterfaces.name: ctDs3ExtensionsNumInterfaces
ctDs3ExtensionsNumInterfaces.description: The number of interfaces on this physical port. This number inidicates the number of entries this physical port uses in the ifTable.

ctDs3ExtensionsLineBuildOut.name: ctDs3ExtensionsLineBuildOut
ctDs3ExtensionsLineBuildOut.description: The line build out setting for this ds3 physical port. Unknown indicates that the setting is neither readable or writable.
